<br>
So here is the question.  How does a poor warrior at lvl 27 bring his piercing, 1hb, and 2hb up to stuff during regular or as close to it as possable play without loosing mass amouts of efficiency?<br>
<br>
~Klaive <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utheaarondome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>theAaronDome</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/30/01 12:48:10 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/theaarondome/blue.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A slight training problem</span><hr size=1> it really isnt a big deal. during normaly play just throw the underachieving weapon skill in the offhand. <br>
<br>
to work on the 2hder skills or to get that 1hder up quick just do some FM,OT,DL,BW sessions. getting a nice little group shouldnt be too hard, and nobody is going to care that you are at your max. <br>
