<br>
Most of time people will let you. You spend a few hours practicing and you're not in a position where a group is depending on your damage output. <p><center><IMG SRC="http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_nametag.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uddarkreaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddarkreaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/30/01 9:19:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://208.162.125.24/eq/family/images/heads/darias_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A slight training problem</span><hr size=1> My 1hb was 50 or so when I decided to work on it.  Three nights later, it's now at 186, and that whole time I was using a piercing weapon in my offhand.  one-handed weapon skills are easy to raise.<br>
