<br>
if it's primarily working on skills get the fastest delay ratio weapon you can get your hands on and go to town<br>
<br>
i worked my 2H blunt skill from 4 to 195 at level 49 in the SolB KPC room, being 7th man was the way, and all i was using was a ketchaka koro mis ( 7 dam / 30 delay ). <br>
<br>
maxxing skills will always take some time; and, as long as you keep plugging away at it you'll get there <p><p align=center><font color=red>Shikarii 'Boom Boom' Apoccalypse<br>52nd Level Champion</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugreblaja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greblaja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/30/01 10:51:16 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A slight training problem</span><hr size=1> The shovel at the orc camp in lake rathe is free <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and has a delay in the 20s - it is likely the fastest 2hb 'weapon' in game.  For the 1h skills, just put them in the offhand, with your good skill in the prime.  The silver lining about starting late on a weapon skill is that you get more swings per level advancement: I, too, have skilled up over 100 skill points over the course of a single level.<br>
